  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Chase debit card, you should take the following steps:\n\n1. **Contact Chase Immediately**: Call Chase customer service at 1-800-935-9935 as soon as possible to report the lost card. This will help prevent unauthorized transactions.\n\n2. **Freeze Your Card**: If you have access to Chase's mobile app or online banking, you can temporarily freeze your card to prevent it from being used while you locate it or until you receive a replacement.\n\n3. **Request a Replacement Card**: Ask Chase to issue you a new debit card. They will deactivate your lost card and send a replacement to your address on file. This typically takes a few business days.\n\n4. **Monitor Account Activity**: Keep a close eye on your account for any unauthorized transactions. Chase has fraud protection services, but it's always good to double-check.\n\n5. **Update Payment Information**: If you use your debit card for automatic payments or have it saved with merchants, be sure to update your payment information once you receive your new card.\n\nBy promptly reporting the loss and taking these steps, you can minimize any potential issues and ensure you have access to your funds without interruption.",
